## Context
Spec writer review: spec says "Header ends at first blank line" but
the parser skips blank lines in the header section (line 81:
if not line.strip(): continue). These disagree.

In practice, existing tickets have a blank line between headers and
the log separator, so the parser works. But the spec promise is
violated — a blank line between two headers would be silently
swallowed instead of ending the header block.

## Actions
1. Decide: change spec or change parser?
   Recommendation: change parser to match spec — first blank line
   in header section transitions to "between headers and log"
2. Add test: header with blank line in middle

## Exit criteria
- Parser and spec agree on blank line semantics
- Existing tickets still parse correctly
